Class RegularExpressionMatchingBacktrackingImpl

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.giddap.dreamfactory.leetcode.onlinejudge.implementations.RegularExpressionMatchingBacktrackingImpl
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    RegularExpressionMatching

    public class RegularExpressionMatchingBacktrackingImpl
extends java.lang.Object
implements RegularExpressionMatching
    弼馬溫注解： Use backtracking approach to search the solution exhaustively.

    If the next char in p is not '*', return false if (1) s is empty or (2) p[0] is not '.' or (3) s[0] does not match p[0]; Otherwise, extend the branch with isMatch(s[1], p[1]);

    If the next char in p is '*': (1) Try skip to p[2] with s first: isMatch(s, p[2]); (2) If the above does not work, for each matching s[i] and p[0], extend the branch on step further with isMatch(s[i + 1], p[2])
